claim.claim-text:
1. A system for applying a catalyst composition to an interior of a hollow substrate comprising: 
coating a substrate with a catalyst composition by immersing the substrate into a vessel containing a bath of coating slurry and applying a vacuum to the partially immersed substrate at an intensity and time sufficient to draw the coating slurry upwardly from the bath into each of a plurality of channels located in the interior of the hollow substrate; 
removing the substrate from the bath; 
rotating the substrate 180°; and 
applying a blast of pressurized air to the substrate at an intensity and time sufficient to distribute the coating slurry within the channels of the substrate to form a uniform coating profile therein.
